jewelled gecko
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:an attractive gecko of widely varying colours and patterns; main populations are in Otago and Banks Peninsula, and east side of Southern Alps.
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: Environment
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: <i> Naultinus gemmeus </i>, aka Otago jewelled gecko
