Quote:  Two types of gecko are also found in the Mackenzie Basin. The Southern Alps gecko (<i>Hoplodactylus aff. maculatus</i> 'Southern Alps') lives near rocky outcrops, screes, boulder banks and rock tumbles. The jewelled gecko (<i>Naultinus gemmeus</i>) lives in forest and shrubland.
